A fault is compensated when the parameter estimation algorithm is active and the precise values of the uncertain parameter is known and considered in control calculations, while the fault is uncompensated when the parameter is set at a constant baseline value (no fault detection), which makes the determination of the reference input position \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
