At the beginning of the study, participants received initial instructions and were requested to don the instrumented heel insole and the knee exoskeleton. Adjustments to the leg attachments were made to ensure that the knee exoskeleton was fitted to the individual body geometry. The participant was asked to walk on the treadmill with the zero-torque mode at a slow walking speed of 0.58m/s. A low torque support profile with \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
